6
00:02:16.051 --> 00:02:19.801
THE FIRST STORY
"THE HUMAN VOICE"


7
00:03:30.426 --> 00:03:32.342
Quiet, Mincia.

8
00:03:36.301 --> 00:03:37.717
Here you go.

9
00:05:41.676 --> 00:05:43.426
No, Mincia, no.

10
00:06:09.842 --> 00:06:12.217
Hello?
Hello? Is that you?


11
00:06:13.092 --> 00:06:14.717
Hello?
Is that you?


12
00:06:14.842 --> 00:06:18.176
I can't hear anything.
I can't hear anything. Hello?


13
00:06:19.051 --> 00:06:21.259
Hello?
You sound very far away.


14
00:06:21.717 --> 00:06:24.092
I can hardly hear you.
Hello?


15
00:06:26.342 --> 00:06:27.551
Hello?
Go on.


16
00:06:28.259 --> 00:06:30.092
Yes.
What's that?


17
00:06:30.926 --> 00:06:32.634
No.
No, it wasn't me.


18
00:06:34.592 --> 00:06:37.926
Yes.
I've just got back.


19
00:06:38.717 --> 00:06:40.384
Why?
Did you call?


20
00:06:44.134 --> 00:06:46.217
No, I was out with Marta.

21
00:06:47.634 --> 00:06:51.467
It must be...
It's half past eleven.


22
00:06:53.551 --> 00:06:55.967
Aren't you at home?

23
00:06:56.676 --> 00:06:59.717
Well, look at the clock
on your mantelpiece.


24
00:07:00.759 --> 00:07:01.967
Ten o'clock?

25
00:07:03.301 --> 00:07:06.092
Ten o'clock...
My clock must be fast.


26
00:07:06.176 --> 00:07:08.092
That's strange.

27
00:07:08.842 --> 00:07:14.176
Last night...
I went to bed very early.


28
00:07:14.676 --> 00:07:17.301
I couldn't sleep so I took a pill.

29
00:07:17.884 --> 00:07:19.967
No, just one, at nine.

30
00:07:20.926 --> 00:07:23.426
I had a nasty headache, so...

31
00:07:24.384 --> 00:07:26.551
I'd been out with Marta all day.

32
00:07:28.551 --> 00:07:32.134
Then I packed your bags.

33
00:07:36.134 --> 00:07:37.717
I'm very strong.

34
00:07:40.467 --> 00:07:42.551
I'm very brave.

35
00:07:44.967 --> 00:07:47.551
Today?
Marta came and picked me up.


36
00:07:49.301 --> 00:07:51.759
Yes, I've just got back from hers.

37
00:07:51.884 --> 00:07:53.551
She's been very sweet.

38
00:07:54.926 --> 00:07:57.092
Really kind.
Just what I needed.


39
00:07:58.342 --> 00:08:00.926
Yes, I did think that.

40
00:08:01.092 --> 00:08:03.926
But she's not selfish.
You were right as usual.


41
00:08:04.759 --> 00:08:05.801
What?

42
00:08:08.926 --> 00:08:11.259
My black satin dress.

43
00:08:12.551 --> 00:08:14.759
Yes, I've still got it on.

44
00:08:16.509 --> 00:08:19.676
No, I haven't been smoking.
Just three cigarettes.


45
00:08:20.467 --> 00:08:22.342
That's all, I promise.

46
00:08:23.634 --> 00:08:25.717
You're very sweet.

47
00:08:26.634 --> 00:08:27.926
Sure.

48
00:08:29.509 --> 00:08:31.426
Haven't you been out?

49
00:08:32.884 --> 00:08:35.301
You stayed at home all day?

50
00:08:35.426 --> 00:08:36.801
What business?

51
00:08:37.926 --> 00:08:39.467
Oh, right.

52
00:08:39.551 --> 00:08:42.092
Hel...
Hello?


53
00:08:42.717 --> 00:08:44.926
Hello...
Hello?


54
00:08:45.842 --> 00:08:47.926
Hello? I can't hear anything.
Hello?


55
00:08:48.801 --> 00:08:50.467
Hello?
Can you hear me?


56
00:08:51.342 --> 00:08:52.759
Hello?
I'm here.


57
00:08:54.801 --> 00:08:56.509
Yes, I'm here.

58
00:08:57.592 --> 00:08:59.759
Yes, I've packed the bags.
I told you.


59
00:09:01.926 --> 00:09:04.967
I put in your letters, and mine too.
Everything.


60
00:09:05.967 --> 00:09:08.551
You can get them picked up
whenever you want.


61
00:09:10.509 --> 00:09:13.467
It's very upsetting.
I understand.


62
00:09:16.134 --> 00:09:18.634
Don't apologise, darling.
I'm the one who...


63
00:09:18.759 --> 00:09:20.467
I'm the one who's not...

64
00:09:21.801 --> 00:09:23.134
who's not loved.

65
00:09:25.634 --> 00:09:27.342
Oh, my love...

66
00:09:28.467 --> 00:09:31.551
No, I didn't think
I'd be this strong either.


67
00:09:32.134 --> 00:09:34.217
Don't admire me too much.

68
00:09:34.676 --> 00:09:36.967
I don't even know what I'm doing.

69
00:09:37.509 --> 00:09:41.551
I get dressed, I go out, I come home.
I'm like a robot.


70
00:09:42.759 --> 00:09:46.092
I may not be so strong tomorrow.
I'm pretty sure I won't.


71
00:09:46.551 --> 00:09:48.259
You, a monster?

72
00:09:49.509 --> 00:09:52.467
No.
No, darling, no.


73
00:09:53.842 --> 00:09:56.842
No, I'm not blaming you for anything.

74
00:09:58.967 --> 00:10:01.134
Yes, of course.

75
00:10:01.259 --> 00:10:03.342
It's only natural.

76
00:10:03.467 --> 00:10:05.967
No, my sweetheart.
What am I supposed to say?


77
00:10:06.634 --> 00:10:11.467
We always agreed we'd be honest with
each other, didn't we?


78
00:10:11.967 --> 00:10:16.467
It would have been terrible if you'd
kept it all from me until the last minute.


79
00:10:17.134 --> 00:10:19.467
The shock would have been unbearable.

80
00:10:19.551 --> 00:10:21.217
But this way, you know,

81
00:10:22.759 --> 00:10:26.217
I've had time to get used to it
and understand your reasons.


82
00:10:27.134 --> 00:10:28.759
What do you mean, acting?

83
00:10:30.092 --> 00:10:32.926
Why, do you want me
to put on an act?


84
00:10:35.426 --> 00:10:37.092
Nothing at all.

85
00:10:37.592 --> 00:10:39.551
I'm really calm.

86
00:10:40.551 --> 00:10:43.676
I mean it.
You'd understand that.


87
00:10:44.509 --> 00:10:46.134
I said you'd understand that.

88
00:10:46.259 --> 00:10:49.634
Do you think
I sound like I'm hiding something?


89
00:10:50.092 --> 00:10:54.217
No. I've decided to be brave
and I will be.


90
00:10:56.551 --> 00:10:58.092
What?

91
00:10:59.342 --> 00:11:01.551
But that was the other day.

92
00:11:02.176 --> 00:11:06.842
It's good to be strong
and prepared, you know.


93
00:11:07.717 --> 00:11:10.592
But when the time comes
it's always a big shock.


94
00:11:10.717 --> 00:11:12.592
No, that's going too far.

95
00:11:13.717 --> 00:11:17.717
As I said, I've had time
to get used to everything.


96
00:11:17.842 --> 00:11:21.301
And you've always
had this ability


97
00:11:21.426 --> 00:11:24.217
to calm me down
and make me feel looked after.


98
00:11:24.342 --> 00:11:25.926
It's frightening.

99
00:11:28.551 --> 00:11:31.176
There were too many obstacles
in our way.


100
00:11:31.676 --> 00:11:34.842
We either had to sacrifice
five years of happiness


101
00:11:34.967 --> 00:11:36.676
or accept the risks.

102
00:11:36.801 --> 00:11:38.801
I took the risk.

103
00:11:38.926 --> 00:11:42.384
And today I'm paying dearly
for all the happiness I've had.


104
00:11:46.467 --> 00:11:48.176
Yes.
Hello?


105
00:11:48.967 --> 00:11:50.592
Hello?
Yes.


106
00:11:51.426 --> 00:11:53.884
I'm paying for it
but I don't regret anything.


107
00:11:54.051 --> 00:11:55.884
Not a single thing.

108
00:11:56.967 --> 00:11:59.092
You?
No, darling...


109
00:12:00.717 --> 00:12:03.551
You're wrong.
You're wrong, my love.


110
00:12:04.467 --> 00:12:08.134
I've got what I deserved
because I wanted too much happiness.


111
00:12:08.717 --> 00:12:10.801
It was like an obsession.

112
00:12:11.842 --> 00:12:13.509
My love...

113
00:12:15.384 --> 00:12:17.551
Don't apologise.
Don't apologise.


114
00:12:18.426 --> 00:12:20.759
It's all my fault, anyway.

115
00:12:20.884 --> 00:12:25.509
Don't you remember
that Sunday in Versailles?


116
00:12:25.967 --> 00:12:30.717
I wanted to come.
I wouldn't let you speak.


117
00:12:30.842 --> 00:12:34.509
I told you I was prepared
to accept everything.


118
00:12:34.592 --> 00:12:36.301
No, let me finish.

119
00:12:36.426 --> 00:12:40.592
I was the one who called you. I came
looking for you. Don't you remember?


120
00:12:41.592 --> 00:12:43.717
No, sweetheart, it was a Tuesday.

121
00:12:43.842 --> 00:12:45.717
Yes, Tuesday 27th.

122
00:12:45.842 --> 00:12:50.092
Your telegram had arrived on Monday

123
00:12:51.551 --> 00:12:53.676
Those dates are fixed in my mind.

124
00:12:55.092 --> 00:12:56.426
What?

125
00:12:56.551 --> 00:12:58.967
I don't know
but I think I'll stay here.


126
00:13:01.717 --> 00:13:03.259
Tomorrow?

127
00:13:03.967 --> 00:13:05.801
You're leaving tomorrow?

128
00:13:06.592 --> 00:13:08.884
I didn't realise it was so soon.

129
00:13:09.051 --> 00:13:10.551
Well...

130
00:13:11.551 --> 00:13:13.467
Hold on a minute, sorry.

131
00:13:14.801 --> 00:13:18.467
Tomorrow morning I'll leave the bags
downstairs with the porter.


132
00:13:19.384 --> 00:13:21.467
Send Giuseppe to pick them up.

133
00:13:21.967 --> 00:13:25.217
Oh, I...
No, it doesn't matter.


134
00:13:25.884 --> 00:13:29.717
I'll stay here or maybe go and spend
a few days in the country with Marta.


135
00:13:30.717 --> 00:13:31.967
Mincia?

136
00:13:33.259 --> 00:13:35.342
Mincia's like a lost soul.

137
00:13:35.467 --> 00:13:38.384
She looks at me,
pricks up her ears and listens.


138
00:13:38.842 --> 00:13:40.759
She's waiting for you.

139
00:13:41.926 --> 00:13:46.176
It feels like she's blaming me, as if
it's my fault you've stopped coming here.


140
00:13:48.592 --> 00:13:51.592
I think it would be best
if you took her back, darling.


141
00:13:52.384 --> 00:13:54.467
She'd be unhappy here.

142
00:13:55.259 --> 00:13:57.926
No, don't worry.

143
00:13:58.967 --> 00:14:02.842
She's not a woman's dog.
I wouldn't know how to deal with her.


144
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:04.842
She'd never go out
if she was with me.


145
00:14:04.967 --> 00:14:07.092
It's best if she stays with you.

146
00:14:07.884 --> 00:14:10.592
She'll soon forget about me,
don't worry.


147
00:14:12.884 --> 00:14:14.967
All right, darling, we'll sort it out.

148
00:14:15.551 --> 00:14:18.384
Look, it's not that complicated.
Please.


149
00:14:18.967 --> 00:14:22.717
Don't worry about that,
you can always say she's a friend's dog.


150
00:14:23.676 --> 00:14:26.801
Mincia's very fond of Giuseppe.
Get him to pick her up.


151
00:14:28.926 --> 00:14:30.217
Look, please...

152
00:14:32.717 --> 00:14:34.801
All right, darling.
All right.


153
00:14:35.509 --> 00:14:36.676
Your gloves?

154
00:14:36.801 --> 00:14:39.884
Oh, those gloves...
Those gloves.


155
00:14:41.217 --> 00:14:43.509
I don't know.
I don't think I've seen them.


156
00:14:43.592 --> 00:14:47.551
I don't know if I put them in the
suitcase. But don't worry about it.


157
00:14:47.634 --> 00:14:51.634
I'll look for them and if I find them
I'll give them to the porter. Don't worry.


158
00:14:53.217 --> 00:14:54.509
What is it, my love?

159
00:14:55.676 --> 00:14:56.884
The letters?

160
00:14:58.801 --> 00:15:00.051
My ones?

161
00:15:00.176 --> 00:15:01.842
Burn them.

162
00:15:03.217 --> 00:15:07.134
Listen, darling,
I want to ask you something.


163
00:15:08.217 --> 00:15:10.301
This may sound really silly.

164
00:15:12.176 --> 00:15:16.926
Look, I just wanted to say
that if you burn them


165
00:15:17.592 --> 00:15:19.259
I'd like you...

166
00:15:20.592 --> 00:15:22.967
I'd like you to keep the ashes

167
00:15:23.134 --> 00:15:25.467
in that tortoiseshell case.

168
00:15:26.217 --> 00:15:29.801
You know, the one I gave you
to put your cigarettes in


169
00:15:29.926 --> 00:15:31.217
and...

170
00:15:36.301 --> 00:15:38.176
No, no...

171
00:15:38.301 --> 00:15:40.967
I'm so stupid, I'm sorry.

172
00:15:42.676 --> 00:15:45.509
Please forgive me, my love.

173
00:15:48.384 --> 00:15:50.259
See?

174
00:15:53.509 --> 00:15:55.926
I was being so strong and then...

175
00:15:57.467 --> 00:15:58.717
Hello?

176
00:15:58.842 --> 00:16:02.259
Hello? What is it?
Why aren't you saying anything?


177
00:16:02.842 --> 00:16:05.134
Yes, I've calmed down.

178
00:16:05.301 --> 00:16:08.509
I've calmed down now.
I'm not crying any more.


179
00:16:10.092 --> 00:16:14.217
I was saying that I'd like you
to keep those ashes. All right?


180
00:16:15.676 --> 00:16:17.134
Thank you, my love.

181
00:16:18.509 --> 00:16:21.759
No, it's not too late for me.
It doesn't matter.


182
00:16:22.592 --> 00:16:25.676
Oh, of course.
You've got to work.


183
00:16:25.801 --> 00:16:29.592
You'd better go to bed now
if you've got to get up early tomorrow.


184
00:16:30.426 --> 00:16:31.801
Tomorrow...

185
00:16:32.592 --> 00:16:33.634
Hello?

186
00:16:34.259 --> 00:16:36.884
Yes, I can hear
a lot of interference too.


187
00:16:37.842 --> 00:16:39.509
But your voice is clear.

188
00:16:39.634 --> 00:16:42.426
It's as if you were here
in the bedroom with me.


189
00:16:43.717 --> 00:16:44.759
Hello?
What...


190
00:16:44.884 --> 00:16:47.884
What's that?
I can't hear you. What did you say?


191
00:16:49.717 --> 00:16:53.967
That's strange.
Your telephone's making strange noises.


192
00:16:54.676 --> 00:16:58.176
It doesn't sound like you're calling
from your own telephone.


193
00:16:59.051 --> 00:17:00.551
Oh, of course.

194
00:17:00.634 --> 00:17:02.092
My love...

195
00:17:02.884 --> 00:17:05.884
My love, I can see you.

196
00:17:08.342 --> 00:17:11.259
You're wearing your scarf,
the red one,


197
00:17:12.592 --> 00:17:15.842
and your sleeves are rolled up
to your elbows.


198
00:17:17.176 --> 00:17:19.301
You've got the receiver
in your left hand


199
00:17:19.426 --> 00:17:23.134
and a pencil in your right
and you're drawing on the blotting paper.


200
00:17:24.509 --> 00:17:25.884
Hearts, stars...

201
00:17:27.717 --> 00:17:28.967
You're laughing?

202
00:17:29.676 --> 00:17:31.842
I've got eyes instead of ears.

203
00:17:33.176 --> 00:17:37.259
No, don't look at me, please.
If you only knew...


204
00:17:37.967 --> 00:17:42.592
I'm not telling you what I did
when I looked at myself in the mirror.


205
00:17:43.509 --> 00:17:46.551
Oh, my God.
My God.


206
00:17:47.134 --> 00:17:51.384
Oh, my darling, my love,
you're so sweet


207
00:17:51.551 --> 00:17:54.592
but you really can't say
that I've got a pretty face.


208
00:17:56.092 --> 00:17:58.551
You know, I actually preferred it

209
00:17:58.717 --> 00:18:01.842
when you used to call me ugly.

210
00:18:02.551 --> 00:18:04.092
My ugly one...

211
00:18:04.801 --> 00:18:06.676
My ugly mug...

212
00:18:08.634 --> 00:18:10.551
Hello?
Hello?


213
00:18:11.342 --> 00:18:12.384
Hello?

214
00:18:12.884 --> 00:18:14.176
Hello?

215
00:18:14.801 --> 00:18:16.092
Hello?

216
00:18:16.217 --> 00:18:17.509
Hello?

217
00:18:18.342 --> 00:18:19.592
Hello?

218
00:18:20.384 --> 00:18:22.092
Hello?

219
00:18:23.051 --> 00:18:24.092
Hello?

220
00:18:31.676 --> 00:18:32.717
Hello?

221
00:18:33.426 --> 00:18:34.467
Hello?

222
00:18:34.842 --> 00:18:35.884
Hel...

223
00:18:36.967 --> 00:18:38.509
Hello?
Giuseppe?


224
00:18:39.051 --> 00:18:41.384
I got cut off
when I was speaking to Mr...


225
00:18:43.759 --> 00:18:45.217
He's not at home?

226
00:18:45.967 --> 00:18:47.926
Oh, I'm such an idiot.

227
00:18:48.092 --> 00:18:52.551
I knew he wasn't going home tonight.
He must have called from the restaurant.


228
00:18:52.676 --> 00:18:53.967
I'm so stupid.

229
00:18:54.134 --> 00:18:56.926
Thank you so much, Giuseppe.
Sorry. Good night.


230
00:21:54.176 --> 00:21:55.217
Hello?

231
00:21:55.342 --> 00:21:57.176
Hello?
Is that you, darling?


232
00:21:58.801 --> 00:22:00.092
We got cut off.

233
00:22:01.176 --> 00:22:02.634
No, I was waiting.

234
00:22:04.176 --> 00:22:05.842
Of course, I understand.

235
00:22:08.634 --> 00:22:10.342
Are you sleepy?

236
00:22:11.509 --> 00:22:13.092
You're very sweet.

237
00:22:13.676 --> 00:22:16.759
It was very kind of you
to call me back.


238
00:22:21.634 --> 00:22:23.342
Yes, I'm still here.
Go on.


239
00:22:23.801 --> 00:22:24.842
Nothing.

240
00:22:26.884 --> 00:22:28.592
Nothing, don't worry.

241
00:22:30.217 --> 00:22:32.551
No, you're wrong, 
I'm not upset.

242
00:22:33.384 --> 00:22:36.342
No, no.
What do you mean, my voice?


243
00:22:36.467 --> 00:22:38.426
It's the same as it was earlier.

244
00:22:38.551 --> 00:22:41.217
No, it's just that I keep on talking

245
00:22:41.342 --> 00:22:43.801
and forget that it's all got to end

246
00:22:44.551 --> 00:22:47.176
and I'll be thrown back
into darkness and silence.


247
00:22:47.759 --> 00:22:50.801
Listen, darling,
I've never lied to you, have I?


248
00:22:52.759 --> 00:22:55.634
Yes, I know,
but I lied to you just now.


249
00:22:55.759 --> 00:22:58.384
I lied to you earlier on the telephone.

250
00:22:58.509 --> 00:23:00.551
Everything I told you was a lie.

251
00:23:00.676 --> 00:23:03.759
I know I've got no hope
and it's pointless,


252
00:23:03.926 --> 00:23:05.426
but lying brings bad luck

253
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:07.551
and I don't like doing it,

254
00:23:07.676 --> 00:23:09.592
even if it's for your sake.

255
00:23:10.967 --> 00:23:13.467
No, don't worry,
it's nothing serious.


256
00:23:14.217 --> 00:23:17.926
I lied to you
when I told you what I was wearing


257
00:23:18.551 --> 00:23:20.634
and that I'd had dinner with Marta.

258
00:23:20.759 --> 00:23:22.426
I didn't have dinner with her.

259
00:23:23.176 --> 00:23:25.384
I'm not wearing my black satin dress.

260
00:23:25.509 --> 00:23:28.092
I'm here in the bed, freezing cold.

261
00:23:28.217 --> 00:23:31.092
All this waiting has frozen me,
you see.


262
00:23:31.217 --> 00:23:34.301
All this getting up,
sitting down, going to bed,


263
00:23:34.426 --> 00:23:37.217
pacing up and down
like a caged animal,


264
00:23:37.384 --> 00:23:40.301
staring at a telephone
that never rang.


265
00:23:40.467 --> 00:23:44.426
All this waiting, waiting, waiting.

266
00:23:45.134 --> 00:23:47.217
I don't even know what for.

267
00:23:47.967 --> 00:23:49.217
Yes, go on.

268
00:23:50.217 --> 00:23:51.842
Go on, tell me.
I'll be calm.


269
00:23:53.134 --> 00:23:55.259
I'll answer all your questions.
Go on.


270
00:23:56.176 --> 00:23:58.259
I'll tell you the truth, I promise.

271
00:24:00.842 --> 00:24:02.134
Here.

272
00:24:03.092 --> 00:24:05.092
No, I haven't eaten anything.

273
00:24:05.217 --> 00:24:07.634
I couldn't.
I've been in a very bad way.


274
00:24:08.426 --> 00:24:12.051
Last night or maybe the night before,
I can't remember when,


275
00:24:12.551 --> 00:24:15.051
I wanted to take a pill
to make me sleep.


276
00:24:16.051 --> 00:24:20.509
And then I thought that if I took more
I'd sleep better.


277
00:24:21.551 --> 00:24:26.134
And if I took them all
I'd sleep without any dreams


278
00:24:26.301 --> 00:24:27.884
and would never wake up.

279
00:24:29.467 --> 00:24:31.092
I'd be dead.

280
00:24:31.842 --> 00:24:33.092
I took 12.

281
00:24:33.759 --> 00:24:36.884
But I did have a dream.
I dreamt about the two of us.


282
00:24:37.551 --> 00:24:39.467
But when I realised that I was alone

283
00:24:39.551 --> 00:24:43.134
and my head wasn't on your shoulder
and my legs weren't next to yours,


284
00:24:43.259 --> 00:24:46.509
I felt that I couldn't go on living.

285
00:24:47.676 --> 00:24:50.509
I was completely frozen,
my heart had stopped beating


286
00:24:50.592 --> 00:24:52.967
but death just wouldn't come.

287
00:24:53.676 --> 00:24:56.926
I was so distressed.
After about an hour I called Marta.


288
00:24:57.092 --> 00:25:01.092
I didn't have the courage
to die alone, my love.


289
00:25:02.259 --> 00:25:06.967
It was four in the morning. Marta came
with the doctor who lives in her building.


290
00:25:07.134 --> 00:25:08.592
My temperature was over40.

291
00:25:08.717 --> 00:25:12.592
They say poisoning yourself is hard
because most people mistake the dose.


292
00:25:13.217 --> 00:25:15.384
No, Marta stayed with me till this
evening.


293
00:25:15.509 --> 00:25:20.634
I made her leave because you'd
promised to call me one last time.


294
00:25:20.759 --> 00:25:23.259
I was afraid
that she wouldn't let me talk to you.


295
00:25:23.384 --> 00:25:27.134
I'd promised myself
that I wouldn't bother you,


296
00:25:27.759 --> 00:25:30.634
I'd let you go without making a scene
and say goodbye


297
00:25:30.801 --> 00:25:33.759
as if we were going
to see each other the next day, but...


298
00:25:34.676 --> 00:25:35.926
Darling, talk to me.

299
00:25:36.134 --> 00:25:39.176
Talk about whatever you like,
so long as you talk to me.


300
00:25:40.134 --> 00:25:41.592
I've suffered so much,

301
00:25:41.676 --> 00:25:45.676
but just the sound of your voice
makes me feel better.


302
00:25:45.801 --> 00:25:47.509
I close my eyes...

303
00:25:47.592 --> 00:25:52.134
Sometimes when I had my head on your
shoulder and my ear on your chest


304
00:25:52.259 --> 00:25:53.509
and you spoke to me,

305
00:25:53.592 --> 00:25:57.467
I'd hear your voice just like
I hear it tonight over the telephone.


306
00:25:58.842 --> 00:26:03.051
No, my love, I was so happy.

307
00:26:03.717 --> 00:26:07.217
I saw her photo
in a magazine at the milliner's studio.


308
00:26:08.467 --> 00:26:12.217
I didn't tell you because I didn't want
to spoil our last weeks together.


309
00:26:13.384 --> 00:26:15.051
Hello?
I can hear music.


310
00:26:15.551 --> 00:26:17.592
I said I can hear music.

311
00:26:17.759 --> 00:26:19.051
Oh, the neighbours.

312
00:26:20.301 --> 00:26:25.051
You should bang on the wall and get
them to turn their gramophone down.


313
00:26:26.217 --> 00:26:27.801
They've got into bad habits

314
00:26:27.926 --> 00:26:31.134
because they know
that you never used to sleep at home.


315
00:26:32.801 --> 00:26:33.842
No, darling, no.

316
00:26:33.967 --> 00:26:37.092
Please don't. If you didn't call back
I'd go out of my mind.


317
00:26:37.967 --> 00:26:40.592
Sorry, darling.
Sorry, darling.


318
00:26:40.717 --> 00:26:44.426
I know this scene I'm making is
unbearable, but try to understand.


319
00:26:44.551 --> 00:26:46.967
Try to understand, my love.
I'm suffering.


320
00:26:47.134 --> 00:26:49.551
I'm suffering for love.
I'm suffering.


321
00:26:49.676 --> 00:26:53.967
And this telephone line is
the only thing that still ties me to you.


322
00:26:56.384 --> 00:27:01.884
The other night, or maybe last night,
I slept with the telephone in the bed.


323
00:27:02.926 --> 00:27:07.301
Yes, I know I'm ridiculous,
but it's the only bond between us now.


324
00:27:07.426 --> 00:27:10.551
I fell asleep waiting for you to call.

325
00:27:11.384 --> 00:27:14.884
You don't know how many dreams I've
had, how many nightmares,


326
00:27:15.092 --> 00:27:18.259
but they were all so vivid.

327
00:27:18.384 --> 00:27:19.967
It's terrible.

328
00:27:20.134 --> 00:27:24.259
For five years I lived for you.
You were the only air I breathed.


329
00:27:24.801 --> 00:27:26.884
I spent my life waiting for you,

330
00:27:27.051 --> 00:27:29.134
thinking you were dead
if you were late,


331
00:27:29.259 --> 00:27:32.134
dying and then coming back to life
when you appeared,


332
00:27:32.217 --> 00:27:34.509
dying of fear whenever you left.

333
00:27:34.592 --> 00:27:37.717
I'm only breathing now
because you're talking to me.


334
00:27:37.884 --> 00:27:41.134
If you hang up now,
I'll die just like that.


335
00:27:42.801 --> 00:27:45.634
Yes, darling, I'll try,
but even if I do fall asleep


336
00:27:45.759 --> 00:27:48.634
there are the dreams,
and then there's waking up again,


337
00:27:48.759 --> 00:27:52.926
and then having to get up,
eat, wash and go out, but go where?


338
00:27:53.051 --> 00:27:54.926
Where?
Where should I go?


339
00:27:55.926 --> 00:27:59.884
My love, I didn't have anything else
to do except be with you.


340
00:28:00.051 --> 00:28:01.759
Only you.

341
00:28:02.467 --> 00:28:04.384
Something to distract me?

342
00:28:05.342 --> 00:28:07.551
After that fateful Sunday evening,

343
00:28:07.634 --> 00:28:11.926
the only time I've had something
to distract me and haven't thought of you


344
00:28:12.092 --> 00:28:15.842
was at the dentist's,
when he touched one of my nerves,


345
00:28:16.384 --> 00:28:18.259
but it was only for a brief moment.

346
00:28:25.842 --> 00:28:26.884
Mincia...

347
00:28:29.801 --> 00:28:31.676
My Mincia...

348
00:28:33.509 --> 00:28:34.551
Yes.

349
00:28:36.634 --> 00:28:38.092
Yes.

350
00:28:40.426 --> 00:28:41.842
Mincia...

351
00:28:42.509 --> 00:28:46.301
Mincia hasn't left her corner for two
days. She won't eat, she won't...


352
00:28:46.426 --> 00:28:48.759
I've tried to call her and stroke her.

353
00:28:48.884 --> 00:28:52.217
She doesn't want to be touched.
I'm pretty sure she'd bite me.


354
00:28:52.342 --> 00:28:54.467
Yes, me.

355
00:28:55.467 --> 00:28:58.342
Believe me, she's a different dog.
She frightens me.


356
00:28:59.217 --> 00:29:03.384
I don't know,
maybe she thinks I've hurt you.


357
00:29:03.884 --> 00:29:07.967
There's no point in that dog staying here
and becoming sick and bad-tempered.


358
00:29:09.426 --> 00:29:12.092
She won't bite anybody at your house.

359
00:29:12.176 --> 00:29:14.884
She'll love the people you love,
I'm sure.


360
00:29:15.051 --> 00:29:18.842
No, I meant she'll grow fond
of the people you live with.


361
00:29:23.592 --> 00:29:28.051
Listen, a few days ago I met that person
whose name begins with S.


362
00:29:28.717 --> 00:29:30.592
Yes, BS, that's right.

363
00:29:31.134 --> 00:29:33.551
She asked me if you had a brother

364
00:29:33.634 --> 00:29:36.551
and if he was the one
whose wedding has been announced.


365
00:29:38.176 --> 00:29:40.467
It felt like
she was commiserating with me.


366
00:29:41.676 --> 00:29:45.217
Yes, whatever.
I couldn't care less.


367
00:29:45.342 --> 00:29:46.717
They can say what they want.

368
00:29:46.842 --> 00:29:50.842
To be honest,
people can't understand our relationship.


369
00:29:51.426 --> 00:29:54.467
Look, most people either love each
other or hate each other.


370
00:29:54.551 --> 00:29:58.717
If something's over, it's over. There are
some things you could never explain.


371
00:30:00.551 --> 00:30:03.717
But it's best to do what I do
and not give a damn.


372
00:30:05.176 --> 00:30:06.926
I'm so stupid.

373
00:30:07.092 --> 00:30:09.051
I'm such an idiot.

374
00:30:09.176 --> 00:30:13.551
I keep on talking, I think
I'm talking to you like I've always done,


375
00:30:13.634 --> 00:30:16.592
but all of a sudden
the truth dawns on me.


376
00:30:20.801 --> 00:30:24.384
Don't worry,
you can't kill yourself twice.


377
00:30:25.842 --> 00:30:28.467
No, I won't take it.
Well, maybe just so I can sleep.


378
00:30:28.551 --> 00:30:32.342
No, I haven't got one.
I'd never be able to buy a gun.


379
00:30:32.426 --> 00:30:35.051
Can you really see me buying a gun?

380
00:30:36.134 --> 00:30:38.967
I can't even tell a lie.

381
00:30:40.134 --> 00:30:44.259
Sometimes lying is necessary or helpful.

382
00:30:44.926 --> 00:30:48.884
If you lied to make our separation...

383
00:30:50.717 --> 00:30:52.884
No, darling,
I'm not saying you're lying.


384
00:30:53.051 --> 00:30:54.467
I'm saying if you lied...

385
00:30:55.676 --> 00:30:57.551
If I knew that...

386
00:30:57.634 --> 00:31:00.467
If you told me you were at home
when you weren't...


387
00:31:02.967 --> 00:31:05.467
No, darling,
just listen to me for a minute.


388
00:31:05.967 --> 00:31:08.384
I didn't mean to
say I don't believe you.

389
00:31:08.509 --> 00:31:11.051
Why are you getting all angry now?

390
00:31:12.551 --> 00:31:15.676
Your voice sounds cruel now.
Why?


391
00:31:16.509 --> 00:31:18.551
It was just an example.
Listen to me.


392
00:31:18.717 --> 00:31:24.801
I was just saying that
if you lied to me out of kindness


393
00:31:24.967 --> 00:31:26.467
and I realised,

394
00:31:27.092 --> 00:31:29.634
my feelings for you wouldn't change.

395
00:31:29.759 --> 00:31:31.509
Do you understand?

396
00:31:32.384 --> 00:31:35.051
No...
Can't you talk from there?


397
00:31:35.926 --> 00:31:37.426
Will you call me back?

398
00:31:39.301 --> 00:31:40.967
You're near here?

399
00:31:43.134 --> 00:31:45.676
You're here...
When you will call me back?


400
00:31:46.301 --> 00:31:49.467
No. Listen.
Listen, my love.


401
00:31:49.551 --> 00:31:51.926
My love, I've hurt you so much.
Listen...


402
00:31:52.134 --> 00:31:53.926
Darling, listen.
Hello?


403
00:32:00.926 --> 00:32:01.967
Oh, God.

404
00:32:04.759 --> 00:32:06.426
Dear God, let him call back.

405
00:32:08.176 --> 00:32:09.801
Dear God, let him call back.

406
00:32:10.926 --> 00:32:12.759
Dear God, let him call back.

407
00:32:15.092 --> 00:32:16.676
Dear God, let him call back.

408
00:32:17.342 --> 00:32:19.217
Dear God, let him call back.

409
00:32:19.342 --> 00:32:22.467
Dear God, let him call back.
Dear God, let him call back.


410
00:32:23.051 --> 00:32:25.634
Dear God, let him call back.
Dear God...


411
00:32:43.384 --> 00:32:44.967
Dear God, let it be him.

412
00:32:46.676 --> 00:32:48.384
Dear God, let it be him.

413
00:32:49.759 --> 00:32:51.467
Dear God, let it be him.

414
00:32:56.176 --> 00:32:58.092
Dear God, let it be him.

415
00:33:08.551 --> 00:33:09.926
Dear God, let it be him.

416
00:33:10.634 --> 00:33:12.342
Dear God, let it be him.

417
00:33:17.842 --> 00:33:19.092
Oh, God.

418
00:33:25.509 --> 00:33:26.967
Dear God, let it be him.

419
00:33:28.426 --> 00:33:30.134
Dear God, let it be him.

420
00:34:13.801 --> 00:34:15.592
Darling.
My love.


421
00:34:15.717 --> 00:34:18.384
My love.
My love...


422
00:34:18.467 --> 00:34:21.426
My love, my love, my love...

423
00:34:21.509 --> 00:34:24.176
My love.
My love...


424
00:34:24.301 --> 00:34:25.759
Yes, I know, it's frightening.

425
00:34:25.884 --> 00:34:29.842
I'll never have the courage, my love.
I'll never have the courage.


426
00:34:30.967 --> 00:34:34.842
Listen, darling, the day after tomorrow
you two will be in Marseilles.


427
00:34:34.967 --> 00:34:38.509
My love,
please promise me one thing,


428
00:34:38.592 --> 00:34:41.592
that you won't stay in the hotel
where we used to go.


429
00:34:42.342 --> 00:34:43.551
Thank you, darling.

430
00:34:43.676 --> 00:34:45.301
Thank you, my love.

431
00:34:45.426 --> 00:34:47.842
No, I don't want to see you again.

432
00:34:47.967 --> 00:34:50.384
We'll never see each other again.

433
00:34:50.509 --> 00:34:52.551
Forgive me, darling.
Forgive me.


434
00:34:54.176 --> 00:34:56.051
My darling love.

435
00:34:56.801 --> 00:34:58.676
Yes, I know, I'll be strong.

436
00:34:59.259 --> 00:35:01.217
Hang up now.

437
00:35:01.342 --> 00:35:03.884
Quickly.
Quickly. Quick...


438
00:35:04.842 --> 00:35:06.134
No!

439
00:35:06.259 --> 00:35:07.884
I love you, darling!

440
00:35:08.551 --> 00:35:10.301
I love you!

441
00:35:10.426 --> 00:35:11.467
I love you.

442
00:35:11.551 --> 00:35:12.759
I love you.

443
00:35:12.884 --> 00:35:15.842
I love you.
I love you...


444
00:35:20.551 --> 00:35:25.134
END OF THE FIRST STORY

445
00:36:12.592 --> 00:36:17.801
"THE MIRACLE"

446
00:36:57.509 --> 00:37:02.676
