447
00:38:06.509 --> 00:38:08.759
Oh, Jesus, Mary and Joseph.

448
00:38:08.884 --> 00:38:11.301
Oh, Jesus, Mary and Joseph.

449
00:38:12.217 --> 00:38:14.509
I knew you would come.

450
00:38:14.592 --> 00:38:16.259
My God, you're so handsome.

451
00:38:16.884 --> 00:38:19.842
Why are you going?
Don't go away.


452
00:38:19.967 --> 00:38:21.634
Can I speak to you?
Can I?


453
00:38:21.759 --> 00:38:23.717
My God, this is such a comfort.

454
00:38:23.842 --> 00:38:28.092
My beautiful saint.
So much happiness, so much joy!


455
00:38:28.217 --> 00:38:32.467
I knew you would come.
Jesus, Mary and Joseph.


456
00:38:32.551 --> 00:38:34.467
My beautiful saint.

457
00:38:34.551 --> 00:38:36.467
I'd always hear your voice.

458
00:38:36.551 --> 00:38:38.551
If I closed my eyes I'd see you,

459
00:38:38.676 --> 00:38:42.051
surrounded by bright light
and smiling at me.


460
00:38:42.176 --> 00:38:46.467
My God, so much laughter,
so much comfort.


461
00:38:46.551 --> 00:38:49.926
My Saint Joseph,
my saint, my beautiful saint.


462
00:38:50.092 --> 00:38:53.801
I worship you, my saint. You're the most
handsome of all the saints.


463
00:38:54.592 --> 00:38:56.134
My Saint Joseph.

464
00:38:56.259 --> 00:38:59.217
Don't go away.
Don't go just like that.


465
00:38:59.842 --> 00:39:02.842
Now you've come
you mustn't leave just like that.


466
00:39:03.592 --> 00:39:07.259
You need to give me your grace.
You need to take me away with you.


467
00:39:07.384 --> 00:39:10.967
It's not hard for you.
You just let me die and it's all done.


468
00:39:11.509 --> 00:39:13.717
And you take me
up to heaven with you

469
00:39:13.842 --> 00:39:16.134
to contemplate the Lord.

470
00:39:23.051 --> 00:39:24.676
You're so beautiful.

471
00:39:24.801 --> 00:39:27.509
Such happiness, such joy.

472
00:39:27.592 --> 00:39:29.259
My Saint Joseph.

473
00:39:29.926 --> 00:39:32.759
You're the kindest saint I know.

474
00:39:33.342 --> 00:39:35.217
If you weren't,

475
00:39:35.342 --> 00:39:39.842
the Lord wouldn't have entrusted
the Madonna and her child to you.


476
00:39:40.967 --> 00:39:44.217
So give me your grace.
You've done it so many times for me.


477
00:39:44.342 --> 00:39:45.801
You've given me everything.

478
00:39:45.926 --> 00:39:47.592
Such kindness.

479
00:39:47.717 --> 00:39:51.634
You'd answer my prayers. If I asked
for something, you'd give it to.


480
00:39:51.717 --> 00:39:54.551
This is the dress
the nuns gave me.


481
00:39:54.634 --> 00:39:56.801
The one I asked you for,
remember?


482
00:39:56.884 --> 00:40:00.884
Now they even give me hot soup
and a place to sleep.


483
00:40:01.384 --> 00:40:04.759
I never ask for anything
from the other saints, but you...


484
00:40:04.884 --> 00:40:08.051
Don't laugh at me.
I know how it works.


485
00:40:08.592 --> 00:40:12.384
All of a sudden you disappear
and I'm left here by myself.


486
00:40:12.842 --> 00:40:15.676
My Saint Joseph,
my beautiful Saint Joseph,


487
00:40:15.801 --> 00:40:20.592
you need to take me up there with you,
to the other land.


488
00:40:21.342 --> 00:40:22.967
So much happiness!

489
00:40:23.134 --> 00:40:26.301
Nobody here will notice anyway
if I die.


490
00:40:26.426 --> 00:40:30.092
Even the goats know how
to get back to the village by themselves.


491
00:40:30.217 --> 00:40:34.551
Beautiful Saint Joseph.
My beautiful saint. Where's your lily?


492
00:40:36.301 --> 00:40:40.051
You're so handsome.
So beautiful.


493
00:40:40.717 --> 00:40:42.634
There's no point in me staying here.

494
00:40:42.717 --> 00:40:46.759
When I told them you'd spoken to me,
you wouldn't believe what they did.


495
00:40:46.884 --> 00:40:48.967
They drove me insane.

496
00:40:49.092 --> 00:40:51.092
They blew a trumpet in my ear
and said,


497
00:40:51.217 --> 00:40:53.967
"This is the trumpet
of the Archangel Gabriel."


498
00:40:54.134 --> 00:40:55.967
They were so mean.

499
00:40:56.134 --> 00:40:59.259
But they don't understand.
They're not worthy.


500
00:40:59.384 --> 00:41:03.217
You're here, though.
Saint Joseph is up here.


501
00:41:03.342 --> 00:41:06.092
He came here to me.
Just to me.


502
00:41:06.259 --> 00:41:08.801
You went through the village
and no one saw you.


503
00:41:08.926 --> 00:41:10.676
They're not worthy.

504
00:41:10.801 --> 00:41:12.676
They're not worthy, but I am.

505
00:41:13.217 --> 00:41:14.884
You're so beautiful.

506
00:41:15.467 --> 00:41:19.259
You know what they keep telling me?
"Mad people can't go to heaven."


507
00:41:19.842 --> 00:41:21.134
For me?

508
00:41:24.801 --> 00:41:27.509
But that's not true, is it?

509
00:41:28.134 --> 00:41:29.842
You know what temptation is?

510
00:41:29.967 --> 00:41:32.176
At one point I kept hearing this voice.

511
00:41:32.342 --> 00:41:35.759
A sweet voice,
just like your voice would sound,


512
00:41:35.842 --> 00:41:41.134
that said, "Throw yourself off, you idiot!
Throw yourself off!"


513
00:41:41.259 --> 00:41:45.467
I'd always get this far,
right here,


514
00:41:45.551 --> 00:41:47.384
but I wasn't brave enough.

515
00:41:47.509 --> 00:41:49.134
Then I'd regret it and say,

516
00:41:49.259 --> 00:41:51.967
"Tomorrow, when the bells ring,

517
00:41:52.176 --> 00:41:55.259
"if Saint Joseph asks again
I'll throw myself off."


518
00:41:55.384 --> 00:41:59.176
But then I understood.
I understood because it wasn't you.


519
00:41:59.301 --> 00:42:01.551
You know who it was?
It was the devil.


520
00:42:02.384 --> 00:42:05.884
He wanted me to kill myself so I'd be
damned and wouldn't go to heaven.


521
00:42:06.051 --> 00:42:08.134
But I was clever.

522
00:42:11.426 --> 00:42:15.384
You know what I'm going to do with you
now? I'm going to do something else.


523
00:42:15.467 --> 00:42:19.551
Look.
You stay still in the air up there.


524
00:42:19.926 --> 00:42:22.301
Up there.
And call me.


525
00:42:22.426 --> 00:42:23.634
I'll come towards you.

526
00:42:23.759 --> 00:42:27.842
And if I get scared and fall,
you'll take my hand and pull me up.


527
00:42:27.926 --> 00:42:31.217
Little by little I'll learn how to do it.
Of course I will.


528
00:42:31.342 --> 00:42:34.092
And then we'll go up there.
Look, up there.


529
00:42:34.217 --> 00:42:36.467
The sanctuary of Saint Michael
is up there.


530
00:42:36.551 --> 00:42:39.259
Why am I telling you?
You know everything.


531
00:42:39.759 --> 00:42:41.509
We'll climb up the bell tower.

532
00:42:41.551 --> 00:42:45.467
You can see all the mountains,
all the houses, the sea.


533
00:42:45.551 --> 00:42:48.967
You'll take me by the hand.
Saint Michael can help me too, can't he?


534
00:42:49.134 --> 00:42:54.092
The three of us will leave the tower
and soar over the Furore Valley.


535
00:42:54.217 --> 00:42:58.426
We'll glide over the sea, drop down to
touch the water with our toes


536
00:42:58.926 --> 00:43:00.384
and then fly back up.

537
00:43:01.301 --> 00:43:03.092
Up.

538
00:43:03.676 --> 00:43:06.551
My beautiful Saint Joseph,
let me die, let me...


539
00:43:10.384 --> 00:43:11.592
If Jesus...

540
00:43:15.301 --> 00:43:16.551
If...

541
00:43:23.759 --> 00:43:27.717
If Jesus came back to earth
I'd like to stay here,


542
00:43:28.551 --> 00:43:30.634
but he's not coming back.

543
00:43:30.759 --> 00:43:34.176
You're an important saint
but you're not Jesus.


544
00:43:34.301 --> 00:43:36.884
He cured the sick
and banished the devil,


545
00:43:37.634 --> 00:43:40.967
but the devil's everywhere
and everybody is sick.


546
00:43:42.301 --> 00:43:46.967
If he came back... Or if he made
the world come to an end...


547
00:43:48.551 --> 00:43:51.884
These are divine plans, aren't they?
I know.


548
00:44:01.051 --> 00:44:03.551
You can't do that, can you?
Can you?


549
00:44:04.301 --> 00:44:06.551
No?
It's easy.


550
00:44:07.717 --> 00:44:09.801
It's nice.
Listen.


551
00:44:16.217 --> 00:44:18.092
It's like heaven.

552
00:44:18.801 --> 00:44:20.676
Just like heaven.

553
00:44:21.884 --> 00:44:24.342
I'm covered in sweat.

554
00:44:25.134 --> 00:44:26.426
Right here.

555
00:44:27.217 --> 00:44:30.551
I'm covered in sweat.
My legs too.


556
00:44:33.551 --> 00:44:34.801
Thank you.

557
00:44:41.217 --> 00:44:43.301
I can hardly see you anymore.

558
00:44:43.967 --> 00:44:46.092
There's a glow around you.

559
00:44:46.217 --> 00:44:47.801
Can you see how you are?

560
00:44:47.926 --> 00:44:52.884
I know there's more and more light
and then you disappear.


561
00:44:53.051 --> 00:44:56.842
Why do you want to go?
I don't want to stay here.


562
00:44:59.801 --> 00:45:01.801
You know, when I was younger,

563
00:45:03.217 --> 00:45:06.509
Casimiro the village idiot
wanted to marry me.


564
00:45:07.801 --> 00:45:09.509
He was such a fool.

565
00:45:10.717 --> 00:45:14.051
If I had children
I wouldn't be able to come with you.


566
00:45:15.092 --> 00:45:17.426
Take me away,
don't leave me here.


567
00:45:18.301 --> 00:45:21.592
Don't leave me here.
It's like heaven.


568
00:45:22.301 --> 00:45:23.967
Just like heaven.

569
00:45:26.967 --> 00:45:29.301
Give me some drink.
I don't feel well.


570
00:45:29.426 --> 00:45:31.509
Give me some drink.
I don't feel well.


571
00:45:56.551 --> 00:45:58.259
My Saint Joseph.

572
00:45:59.426 --> 00:46:00.801
My Saint Joseph.

573
00:46:03.592 --> 00:46:05.676
He took the bread and broke it

574
00:46:06.676 --> 00:46:11.301
and an angel of the Lord
appeared to him in a dream and said,


575
00:46:12.092 --> 00:46:17.467
"Joseph, son of David,
be not afraid to take Mary as your wife


576
00:46:18.842 --> 00:46:21.676
"because that which is conceived in
her..."


577
00:46:25.259 --> 00:46:26.842
My Saint Joseph.

578
00:46:27.759 --> 00:46:30.384
Throw away my body
and take my soul.


579
00:46:31.592 --> 00:46:34.176
Throw it away without any clothes on.

580
00:46:35.759 --> 00:46:37.634
Saint Joseph...

581
00:46:37.759 --> 00:46:40.259
Saint Joseph, please help me.

582
00:46:40.384 --> 00:46:42.259
It's like heaven.

583
00:46:43.217 --> 00:46:45.134
Heaven on earth.

584
00:46:46.051 --> 00:46:48.217
The madwoman has received your
grace.


585
00:46:48.884 --> 00:46:49.926
I...

586
00:46:50.759 --> 00:46:51.801
I feel ill.

587
00:46:53.717 --> 00:46:54.967
I'm sick.

588
00:48:22.509 --> 00:48:23.967
Come on, let's go.

589
00:48:24.842 --> 00:48:26.134
Let's go.

590
00:50:00.134 --> 00:50:02.051
Brother Raffaele!

591
00:50:10.509 --> 00:50:12.676
- Good day, Brother Raffaele.
- Good day.


592
00:50:12.801 --> 00:50:15.717
Tell me, saints can appear to us,
can't they?


593
00:50:15.842 --> 00:50:17.717
- Yes, I always see them.
- Where?


594
00:50:17.842 --> 00:50:21.092
I always see the Madonna..
She appears whenever she wishes.


595
00:50:21.217 --> 00:50:24.509
- Can we see them with our eyes?
- Of course.


596
00:50:25.634 --> 00:50:27.842
- Who have you seen?
- The Madonna.


597
00:50:27.967 --> 00:50:31.176
- Do you see her all the time?
- All day long.


598
00:50:31.301 --> 00:50:34.134
- Jesus! Is she pretty?
- She's beautiful.


599
00:50:36.634 --> 00:50:41.551
You know what? I've seen Saint Joseph.
Just now, on Capo d'Orso.


600
00:50:41.967 --> 00:50:44.551
And I spoke to him.
A lot.


601
00:50:44.634 --> 00:50:47.801
He was so handsome, Brother Raffaele.
I want to see him again.


602
00:50:48.467 --> 00:50:50.384
Maybe he'll come back the same way.

603
00:50:50.509 --> 00:50:53.342
- You think so?
- When the Lord wishes...


604
00:50:53.467 --> 00:50:55.176
- What is it?
- How can I put it?


605
00:50:55.259 --> 00:50:58.176
- There's been a miracle.
- What do you mean, a miracle?


606
00:50:58.301 --> 00:50:59.884
You've never had visions?

607
00:51:00.092 --> 00:51:03.551
I've been here for 20 years
and I've never seen a miracle.


608
00:51:03.676 --> 00:51:06.884
- What do you say, Brother Raffaele?
- He's crazy.


609
00:51:07.051 --> 00:51:09.467
Haven't you ever had a vision?

610
00:52:26.217 --> 00:52:27.467
Take the apple.

611
00:52:30.759 --> 00:52:33.134
Take the apple.

612
00:52:33.217 --> 00:52:34.884
Give it to me.

613
00:52:35.051 --> 00:52:36.884
Give it to me.

614
00:52:44.134 --> 00:52:47.842
I want the apple.
Give it to me.


615
00:53:31.426 --> 00:53:33.842
Will you give it to me?

616
00:53:34.676 --> 00:53:36.884
- What?
- The apple.


617
00:53:42.467 --> 00:53:46.176
Come on.
Wait. Wait.


618
00:54:17.051 --> 00:54:18.301
Hey, Nanni.

619
00:54:33.051 --> 00:54:37.967
Lovely babies. Lovely babies.
Down you go.


620
00:55:20.092 --> 00:55:21.926
- Hey, Nanni.
- Nanni?


621
00:55:23.426 --> 00:55:25.467
Jesus!
She's pregnant.


622
00:55:25.551 --> 00:55:28.176
Nanni, you're pregnant.
Did you know?


623
00:55:40.884 --> 00:55:42.592
Don't touch me.

624
00:55:42.717 --> 00:55:44.176
Don't touch me.

625
00:55:45.842 --> 00:55:49.092
- The grace of the Lord.
- The grace of the Lord, my foot!


626
00:57:18.842 --> 00:57:20.717
Hold on a minute.

627
00:57:37.592 --> 00:57:39.884
- Have you been to confession?
- No.


628
00:57:41.134 --> 00:57:44.884
You should go to confession.
You need to be at peace with the Lord.


629
00:57:45.051 --> 00:57:48.426
Why? I am at peace with the Lord.
He loves me.


630
00:57:48.551 --> 00:57:52.592
The Lord loves us all, but it's always
good to listen to a confessor's advice.


631
00:57:52.717 --> 00:57:54.176
You're in sin.

632
00:57:54.301 --> 00:57:57.801
Sin?
Mother, I'm in the grace of the Lord.


633
00:57:58.551 --> 00:58:00.301
You don't know what you're saying.

634
00:58:00.426 --> 00:58:04.259
Listen to me. You need to listen to a
confessor's advice.


635
00:58:04.384 --> 00:58:09.509
What does he know?
I'm at peace with the Lord. He loves me.


636
00:58:10.467 --> 00:58:12.342
He's given me his grace.

637
00:58:13.051 --> 00:58:15.967
- Listen.
- I know, it's my conscience.


638
00:58:18.426 --> 00:58:20.301
My conscience...

639
00:58:21.676 --> 00:58:23.342
My conscience is clear.

640
00:58:28.134 --> 00:58:29.926
My conscience...

641
00:59:56.176 --> 01:00:00.967
Get out! Get out!
Get out of here!


642
01:00:01.092 --> 01:00:03.259
- Get out!
- What are you doing?


643
01:00:03.926 --> 01:00:06.301
Leave my spot alone.

644
01:00:06.426 --> 01:00:08.801
Leave my spot alone.

645
01:00:09.676 --> 01:00:14.051
- You gave it to me. Leave it alone.
- Go away!


646
01:00:14.217 --> 01:00:16.926
You gave it to me.
You're the devil!


647
01:00:17.092 --> 01:00:19.801
The devil's in your body.

648
01:00:20.592 --> 01:00:24.176
She's crazy.

649
01:00:24.301 --> 01:00:26.092
Give it to me.

650
01:00:26.217 --> 01:00:28.217
He won't give it back.

651
01:00:28.342 --> 01:00:31.509
You're the devil.
Leave me alone.


652
01:00:32.259 --> 01:00:35.551
That's enough.
That really is enough.


653
01:00:35.676 --> 01:00:40.342
Get out!
Go away!


654
01:00:44.551 --> 01:00:46.592
He's telling me to get out.

655
01:00:47.967 --> 01:00:51.801
- That was my spot.
- Get out!


656
01:00:52.842 --> 01:00:57.342
You gave it to me.
Now you want it back.


657
01:00:57.467 --> 01:01:00.176
I even said a prayer for you.

658
01:01:02.051 --> 01:01:06.676
- Get out.
- You're the devil! You're the devil!


659
01:01:06.759 --> 01:01:10.551
You're the devil!
You're the devil!


660
01:01:10.634 --> 01:01:14.342
Get out!
Go away!


661
01:01:27.134 --> 01:01:29.634
I even said a prayer for you.

662
01:02:46.426 --> 01:02:48.676
Hey, Nanni.
Come here.


663
01:02:48.759 --> 01:02:49.801
Me?

664
01:02:49.926 --> 01:02:54.342
We're not going to bite you, Nanni.
Don't be afraid.


665
01:02:54.467 --> 01:02:56.801
- Me?
- Yes. Come here a minute.


666
01:02:58.217 --> 01:02:59.717
Hold this for me.

667
01:03:01.259 --> 01:03:02.842
Of course.

668
01:03:05.384 --> 01:03:08.676
Felice's gone to Minori.
He's not back yet.


669
01:03:08.801 --> 01:03:12.134
When he goes out
he gets lost in the streets.


670
01:03:12.259 --> 01:03:14.967
When we've finished
you can fetch me some water.


671
01:03:15.134 --> 01:03:17.842
- I can't tire myself out.
- I'll pay you.


672
01:03:17.926 --> 01:03:21.092
- I know, but I can't.
- Come on, it's only a jug of water.


673
01:03:21.217 --> 01:03:26.301
- Will you help me out tomorrow?
- Thank you, but I can't work.


674
01:03:26.426 --> 01:03:28.509
- Why not?
- Well...


675
01:03:28.592 --> 01:03:29.884
That's nonsense.

676
01:03:30.592 --> 01:03:34.384
I stopped working two hours
before giving birth, and I had twins.


677
01:03:34.509 --> 01:03:37.634
- Yes, I know, but...
- You need to sort yourself out.


678
01:03:37.717 --> 01:03:41.759
You're going to have a baby.
You need to put some money aside.


679
01:03:43.342 --> 01:03:45.967
He doesn't need anything.

680
01:03:46.092 --> 01:03:47.884
I can't tire myself out.

681
01:03:48.051 --> 01:03:52.301
If won't even matter if I die of hunger,
but I need to respect him.


682
01:03:52.384 --> 01:03:55.051
Hey, Nanni.
Come here.


683
01:03:55.176 --> 01:03:57.759
Nanni.
Come here.


684
01:03:58.676 --> 01:04:00.384
Yes...
I'm coming.


685
01:04:00.509 --> 01:04:02.384
- Excuse me.
- Off you go.


686
01:04:02.509 --> 01:04:05.217
- Me?
- Hey, Nanni.


687
01:04:05.342 --> 01:04:07.926
- I'm sorry.
- Don't worry.


688
01:04:09.342 --> 01:04:13.134
Nanni, you've deigned to mingle
with us poor mortals. What an honour.


689
01:04:13.217 --> 01:04:15.551
- Me?
- Yes, you.


690
01:04:15.676 --> 01:04:19.759
You disappeared.
You turned your nose up at us.


691
01:04:23.509 --> 01:04:25.384
Look!
It's Nanni.


692
01:04:29.426 --> 01:04:31.592
- No, don't...
- Why don't you speak to me?


693
01:04:31.717 --> 01:04:35.509
Leave me alone.
What's going on?


694
01:04:35.634 --> 01:04:38.634
- Why is she crying?
- It's the emotion.


695
01:04:38.801 --> 01:04:40.259
The Lord has touched you.

696
01:04:40.384 --> 01:04:42.801
- Come with us.
- No...


697
01:04:44.467 --> 01:04:47.551
- You know who she thinks she is?
- You shouldn't tease her.


698
01:04:47.634 --> 01:04:50.801
- She's become even more stupid.
- Poor woman. Leave her alone.


699
01:04:50.926 --> 01:04:52.717
Poor woman, my foot!

700
01:04:52.842 --> 01:04:54.342
Come on!

701
01:04:54.509 --> 01:04:55.551
Well?

702
01:04:56.509 --> 01:04:58.926
I've always been
outside the Lord's house.


703
01:04:59.592 --> 01:05:01.467
Always outside the Lord's house

704
01:05:01.551 --> 01:05:04.551
because I was afraid
to be amongst you.


705
01:05:05.551 --> 01:05:08.759
I was afraid you'd think I was mad,
but actually...


706
01:05:08.884 --> 01:05:11.509
- What's this?
- You need to wear it like this.


707
01:05:11.967 --> 01:05:15.426
Nanni, they're doing you a great honour,
can't you see?


708
01:05:15.967 --> 01:05:18.926
You're going to throw me out,
aren't you?


709
01:05:19.092 --> 01:05:22.717
This is the Lord's will.
I was meant to come to you.


710
01:05:22.842 --> 01:05:24.092
- Nanni!
- Yes?


711
01:05:24.759 --> 01:05:25.801
Here you go, Nanni.

712
01:05:27.759 --> 01:05:29.051
Nanni!

713
01:05:30.551 --> 01:05:31.801
Nanni!

714
01:05:34.509 --> 01:05:36.759
- Is this for me?
- Yes, it's for you.


715
01:05:37.509 --> 01:05:39.384
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.


716
01:05:40.509 --> 01:05:44.551
- Come with us.
- Thank you.


717
01:06:20.426 --> 01:06:23.134
- Nanni, it suits you.
- No...


718
01:06:23.717 --> 01:06:27.842
No...
What are you doing?


719
01:06:35.926 --> 01:06:39.634
My God, forgive them,
they don't know what they're doing.


720
01:06:42.967 --> 01:06:44.051
No!

721
01:06:44.676 --> 01:06:46.259
That's enough!

722
01:06:46.342 --> 01:06:47.551
No!

723
01:06:47.676 --> 01:06:49.217
That's enough!

724
01:07:34.384 --> 01:07:36.301
They're wicked.

725
01:07:39.801 --> 01:07:44.092
My blessed son,
don't worry, I'll protect you.


726
01:07:44.259 --> 01:07:45.634
My God...

727
01:08:55.759 --> 01:08:58.551
Holy son, holy son.

728
01:08:58.592 --> 01:09:00.342
Beautiful son.

729
01:09:00.467 --> 01:09:03.676
Holy son, holy son.

730
01:09:04.551 --> 01:09:07.926
I'm not worthy, 
I'm too lowly.

731
01:09:08.592 --> 01:09:10.134
My God, help me.

732
01:09:10.634 --> 01:09:12.509
May your will be done.

733
01:11:49.592 --> 01:11:51.342
Oh, God.

734
01:12:34.842 --> 01:12:36.134
Help...

735
01:12:37.051 --> 01:12:38.634
Help...

736
01:16:57.217 --> 01:16:58.676
Oh, God.

737
01:17:07.134 --> 01:17:10.926
God...
God, God, God, God, God.


738
01:17:13.342 --> 01:17:15.217
Help...

739
01:17:17.384 --> 01:17:20.051
God, help me.
God, help me.


740
01:17:20.176 --> 01:17:23.217
God, help me.
God, help me.


741
01:17:41.509 --> 01:17:44.467
My God...

742
01:18:10.467 --> 01:18:11.676
God...

743
01:18:11.759 --> 01:18:13.176
